@startuml
left to right direction
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 12
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #F8FAFC
  BorderColor #475569
}
skinparam database {
  BackgroundColor #FEF3C7
  BorderColor #B45309
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #FFF7ED
  BorderColor #C2410C
}

title EduSecure Current-State Data Flow Diagram - Level 1

rectangle "Client Boundary" {
  rectangle "Student\n<<External Entity>>" as Student #E0F2FE
  rectangle "Assignment-owning Lecturer\n<<External Entity>>" as Lecturer #E0F2FE
  rectangle "Admin\n<<External Entity>>" as Admin #E0F2FE
  rectangle "Authenticator App\n<<External Entity>>" as Authenticator #E0F2FE
  database "D0 Browser sessionStorage\npending MFA challenge only\n(no JWT)" as D0
}

rectangle "EduSecure Application Boundary" {
  rectangle "P1 Auth and Session Handling\nAuthController + AuthService" as P1 #DBEAFE
  rectangle "P2 MFA Challenge Handling\nMfaService" as P2 #DBEAFE
  rectangle "P3 Submission Protection and Retrieval\nSubmissionService" as P3 #DBEAFE
  rectangle "P4 Grade Integrity Handling\nGradeService" as P4 #DBEAFE
  rectangle "P6 Space Ownership and Membership Handling\nSpaceService" as P6 #DBEAFE
  rectangle "P5 Audit Integrity Recording\nAuditService" as P5 #DBEAFE
}

rectangle "Persistence Boundary" {
  database "D1 PostgreSQL\nusers, roles, assignments, spaces, memberships,\nMFA metadata, submission metadata, grades, audit logs" as D1
  database "D2 Submission Ciphertext Store\nciphertext blobs by storedFileReference" as D2
}

Student --> P1 : registration/login\n/api/auth/* requests
Lecturer --> P1 : login/logout\n/api/auth/* requests
Admin --> P1 : login/logout\n/api/auth/* requests
P1 --> Student : Set-Cookie auth session\ncurrent-user response
P1 --> Lecturer : Set-Cookie auth session\ncurrent-user response
P1 --> Admin : Set-Cookie auth session\ncurrent-user response
P1 --> D1 : read/write users, roles,\npassword hashes, session claims input
P1 --> P2 : start MFA challenge when required
P1 --> D0 : store MFA pending challenge metadata

Student --> P2 : MFA setup / verify / disable requests
Lecturer --> P2 : MFA setup / verify / disable requests
Admin --> P2 : MFA setup / verify / disable requests
P2 --> Authenticator : otpauth URI / manual key
Authenticator --> P2 : TOTP code
P2 --> D1 : encrypted MFA secret, challenge records,\nrecovery-code hashes
P2 --> P1 : authenticated MFA result for cookie issuance
P2 --> D0 : clear pending challenge after success/failure path

Student --> P3 : space-scoped assignment submission / metadata / content requests
Lecturer --> P3 : owner-scoped submission review / content access requests
Admin --> P3 : oversight submission review / content access requests
P3 --> D1 : assignment lookup + current space membership,\nsubmission metadata, digest, signature, verification state, wrapped key metadata
P3 --> D2 : store ciphertext / read ciphertext
P3 --> Student : metadata-only response\nor plaintext on explicit content retrieval
P3 --> Lecturer : metadata-only response\nor plaintext on authorised owned-assignment retrieval
P3 --> Admin : metadata-only response\nor plaintext on authorised oversight retrieval
P3 --> P5 : SUBMISSION_CREATED\nSUBMISSION_VERIFIED / FAILED\nSUBMISSION_CONTENT_ACCESSED

Lecturer --> P4 : owner-scoped create/update/retrieve grade requests
Admin --> P4 : oversight create/update/retrieve grade requests
Student --> P4 : own-grade retrieval request
P4 --> D1 : read verified submission state,\nassignment visibility, and write/read grade records
P4 --> Lecturer : owned-assignment grade responses
P4 --> Admin : oversight grade responses
P4 --> Student : own-grade response only\nwhile assignment remains visible
P4 --> P5 : GRADE_CREATED / GRADE_UPDATED

Lecturer --> P6 : create/list/detail/update\nowned space membership requests
Admin --> P6 : global space management requests
Student --> P6 : enrolled-space list/detail requests
P6 --> D1 : read/write spaces, memberships,\nownership, membership counts
P6 --> Lecturer : owned-space responses + roster data
P6 --> Admin : oversight space responses + roster data
P6 --> Student : enrolled-space responses only\n(no full roster disclosure)
P6 --> P5 : SPACE_CREATED / UPDATED\nSPACE_STUDENT_ADDED / REMOVED

P5 --> D1 : append audit log row with\nHMAC-SHA-256 integrity chain

note right of P3
Plaintext enters the backend once for submission handling.
The backend computes the SHA-256 digest,
creates/verifies signature metadata,
then encrypts content at rest with AES-GCM.
Lecturer access is limited to assignments they own.
Student self-service reads are limited to
assignments still visible through current
space membership.
end note

note right of D2
Ciphertext is stored separately from PostgreSQL metadata.
Normal metadata responses do not expose
storedFileReference, nonce values,
or wrapped content-encryption keys.
end note

note right of P6
Spaces already follow the same owner-scoped lecturer model:
- lecturer manages only created spaces
- admin can manage any space
- students see only enrolled spaces and no full roster
end note
@enduml


